<p><strong>Sauvignon Blanc</strong> emerged from France's Loire Valley and Bordeaux regions, where cool climates preserved its naturally high acidity and herbaceous character. The grape contains high levels of methoxypyrazines—the same compounds found in bell peppers—which create its distinctive grassy, green notes.</p>

